<TITLE> Gazipur garment workers take to streets for pay </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Gazipur, June 8 (bdnews24.com) -- Hundreds of garment workers demonstrated on Dhaka-Tangail highway Friday, demanding their wages for at least three months, police said. The half-an-hour roadblock led to a long traffic jam. Later police and RAB officers controlled the situation. Workers of Aimon Garments in Kaliakoir upazila complained of living without money for days. Kaliakoir police chief Shahjahan Kabir said: "The workers demonstrated for pay. Later they went back to work when the employer promised to pay their salaries Wednesday." "Demonstration is no new incident for Aimon Garments," an officer from Kaliakoir Police Station told bdnews24.com, asking not to be named. bdnews24.co
